<author><name><![CDATA[Shehzad Sattar]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-07-30T01:25:51+01:00</updated>
<published>2017-07-30T01:25:51+01:00</published>
<id>https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1507&amp;p=1608#p1608</id>
<link href="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1507&amp;p=1608#p1608"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Quran &amp; its Sciences • Tafseer: Disobeying One Is Like Disobeying All]]></title>

<category term="Quran &amp; its Sciences" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=6" label="Quran &amp; its Sciences"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1507&amp;p=1608#p1608"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Tafseer: Disobeying One Is Like Disobeying All</span></strong><br /><br />بسم الله والحمد لله والصلاة والسلام على رسول الله ، وبعد<br /><br /><ul>* Opposing the Sunnah of Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم is like opposing the Sunnah of all the Prophets and Messengers before him.<br />* Disobeying one Messenger is like disobeying all the Messengers.<br />* Opposing one Messenger is like opposing all the Messengers.<br />* Disbelieving in one Messenger is like disbelieving in all the Messengers.</ul><br />Allaah تعالى says:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ قَوْمُ نُوحٍ الْمُرْسَلِينَ﴾</ul><br />{The people of Nooh belied the Messengers.} [Surah al-Shu`raa (26): 105]<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Tafseer of al-Baghawee رحمه الله:</span></strong><br /><br />“It was said to al-Hasan al-Basree رحمه الله: O Abu Sa`eed! Don’t you see the statement of Allaah تعالى:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ قَوْمُ نُوحٍ الْمُرْسَلِينَ﴾</ul><br />{The people of Nooh belied the Messengers.} [Surah al-Shu`raa (26): 105]<br /><br />And His تعالى saying:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ عَادٌ الْمُرْسَلِينَ﴾</ul><br />{(The people of) `Aad denied the Messengers.} [Surah al-Shu`raa (26): 123]<br /><br />And also His تعالى saying:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ ثَمُودُ الْمُرْسَلِينَ﴾</ul><br />{(The people of) Thamood denied the Messengers.} [Surah al-Shu`raa (26): 141]<br /><br />Whereas (each group of people) were sent with only one Messenger? He said: “The last one of them (i.e. Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) came with what the first one came with. So, if they deny any one of them, it is like denying all the Messengers.”<br />--end of quote<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Tafseer al-Muyassar:</span></strong><br /><br />“The people of Nooh عليه السلام disbelieved in the Message brought to them by their Prophet. By doing this, they disbelieved in all the Messengers. This is because every Messenger commanded (his people) to believe in all the Messengers.”<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Tafseer of Ibn Katheer رحمه الله:</span></strong><br /><br />“Here Allaah tells us about His servant and Messenger Nooh عليه السلام, who was the first Messenger, sent by Allaah to the people of earth after they started to worship idols. Allaah sent him to forbid that and to warn people of the consequences of idol worship. But his people belied him and continued their evil practice of worshipping idols besides Allaah. Allaah revealed that their disbelieving in him was akin to disbelieving in all the Messengers, So Allaah تعالى said:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ قَوْمُ نُوحٍ الْمُرْسَلِينَ - إِذْ قَالَ لَهُمْ أَخُوهُمْ نُوحٌ أَلاَ تَتَّقُونَ ﴾</ul><br />{The people of Nooh belied the Messengers. When their brother Nooh said to them: &quot;Will you not have Taqwa?”}” [Surah al-Shu`raa (26): 105-106]<br />--end of quote<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Tafseer of al-Sa`dee رحمه الله:</span></strong><br /><br />“Allaah تعالى mentions the denial of the people of Nooh about their Messenger Nooh عليه السلام and what he said to them and what they replied back to him, and how their end was.<br /><br />He تعالى said:<br /><br /><ul>﴿كَذَّبَتْ قَوْمُ نُوحٍ الْمُرْسَلِينَ﴾</ul><br />{The people of Nooh belied the Messengers.} meaning: all of them. He نعالى made their denial of Nooh عليه السلام like denying all the Messengers. This is because, all of them, their call was one, their message was one. Denying (the Messengership of) anyone of them is akin to denying all of them.”<br />--end of quote<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sun Jul 30, 2017 1:25 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Shehzad Sattar]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-07-30T00:27:34+01:00</updated>
<published>2017-07-30T00:27:34+01:00</published>
<id>https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1502&amp;p=1603#p1603</id>
<link href="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1502&amp;p=1603#p1603"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Quran &amp; its Sciences • “And We Have Made Some Of You As A Trial For Others: Will You Have Patience. [Soorah Al-Furqaan]”]]></title>

<category term="Quran &amp; its Sciences" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=6" label="Quran &amp; its Sciences"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1502&amp;p=1603#p1603"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">“And We Have Made Some Of You As A Trial For Others: Will You Have Patience.  [Soorah Al-Furqaan]”</span></strong><br /><br />Allaah (The Most High) said:<br /><br />وَجَعَلْنَا بَعْضَكُمْ لِبَعْضٍ فِتْنَةً أَتَصْبِرُونَ<br /><br />And We have made some of you as a trial for others: will you have patience.  [Soorah Al-Furqaan]<br /><br />Imaam Ibnul Qayyim (rahimahullaah) said:<br /><br />This is universal amongst all the creation- they are put to trial by one another. <br /><br />Those whom the Messengers are sent to are a trial for the Messengers—in calling them to the truth, exercising patience in facing their harm and bearing the difficulty in conveying the Message of their Lord.<br /><br /> And the Messengers are a trial for those whom they have been sent to, as to whether they will obey and aid them, and testify to the truth of that which they have been sent with; or whether they will disbelieve, reject and fight them.<br /><br />The ignorant people are a trial for the scholars, as to whether they will teach and advise them, whilst exercising patience in teaching, advising, guiding them and been constant in that.<br /><br />And the scholars are a trial for the ignorant people, as to whether they will obey them and follow their example.<br /><br />The subjects are a trial for the kings and the kings are a trial for the subjects.<br /><br />The poor people are a trial for the rich people and the rich people are a trial for the poor people.<br /><br />The weak people are a trial for the strong people and the strong people are a trial for the weak people.<br /><br />The leaders are put to trial by those who follow them and those who follow are put to trial by way of the leaders.<br /><br />The slave master is put to trial by way of his slaves and the slaves are put to trial by way of the slave master.<br /><br />A man is put to trial by way of his wife and his wife is put to trial by way of him.<br />The men are put to trial by way of women and women are put to trial by way of men.<br /><br />The believers are put to trial by way of the disbelievers and the disbelievers are put to trial by way of the believers.<br /><br />Those who enjoin good and forbid evil are put to trial by way of those whom they command good and forbid from evil, and those commanded with good and forbidden from evil are put to trial by way of those who command them with good and forbid them from evil…..<br /><br /><em>[Source: Ighaathatul Luhfaan: 2/170-172]</em><br />                         سؤال عن لغات الجن - الموقع الرسمي للإمام ابن باز<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.ibnbaz.org.sa">www.ibnbaz.org.sa</a><!-- w --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sun Jul 30, 2017 12:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
